clearTasks.doc: Clears all completed tasks from the specified task list. The affected tasks are marked as hidden and are no longer returned by default when retrieving all tasks for a task list. Returns no data (only a status code). Authentication is required.

tasklist.doc: Task list identifier. To refer to the authenticated user's default task list, use the special value @default.

createTasks.doc: Creates a new task on the specified task list. Returns a copy of the created Task Resource. Authentication is required.

tasklist.doc: Task list identifier. To refer to the authenticated user's default task list, use the special value @default.

fields.doc: Selector specifying a subset of fields to include in the response. Use for better performance.

parent.doc: Specify the task's parent task ID. No parameter indicates an insertion or a move to the top level of the task list.

previous.doc: Specify the task's previous task ID. No parameter indicates an insertion or a move to the first position in the sublist.

createUserTaskList.doc: Creates a new task list and adds it to the authenticated user's task lists. Returns a copy of the created Tasklist Resource. Authentication is required.

fields.doc: Selector specifying a subset of fields to include in the response. Use for better performance.

deleteTask.doc: Deletes the specified task from the task list. Returns no data (only a status code). Authentication is required.

tasklist.doc: Task list identifier. To refer to the authenticated user's default task list, use the special value @default.

deleteUserTaskList.doc: Deletes the authenticated user's specified task list. Returns no data (only a status code). Authentication is required.

tasklist.doc: Task list identifier. To refer to the authenticated user's default task list, use the special value @default.

getTask.doc: Returns the specified Task Resource. Authentication is required.

tasklist.doc: Task list identifier. To refer to the authenticated user's default task list, use the special value @default.

fields.doc: Selector specifying a subset of fields to include in the response. Use for better performance.

getUserTaskList.doc: Returns the authenticated user's specified Tasklist Resource. Authentication is required.

tasklist.doc: Task list identifier. To refer to the authenticated user's default task list, use the special value @default.

fields.doc: Selector specifying a subset of fields to include in the response. Use for better performance.

listTasks.doc: Returns all Task Resources in the specified task list. Authentication is required.

tasklist.doc: Task list identifier. To refer to the authenticated user's default task list, use the special value @default.

fields.doc: Selector specifying a subset of fields to include in the response. Use for better performance.

maxResults.doc: The maximum number of elements to return with this request. Default: maxResults=20. Maximum allowable value: maxResults=100.

completedMax.doc: Upper bound for a task's completion date (as an RFC 3339 timestamp) to filter by. Default: completedMax=2031-01-01. Use the RFC 3339 timestamp format. For example: 2010-08-09T10:57:00.000-08:00

completedMin.doc: Lower bound for a task's completion date (as an RFC 3339 timestamp) to filter by. Default: completedMin=1970-01-01. Use the RFC 3339 timestamp format. For example: 2010-08-09T10:57:00.000-08:00

dueMax.doc: Upper bound for a task's due date (as an RFC 3339 timestamp) to filter by. Default: dueMax=2031-01-01. Use the RFC 3339 timestamp format. For example: 2010-08-09T10:57:00.000-08:00

dueMin.doc: Lower bound for a task's due date (as an RFC 3339 timestamp) to filter by. Default: dueMin=1970-01-01. Use the RFC 3339 timestamp format. For example: 2010-08-09T10:57:00.000-08:00

showCompleted.doc: Specify whether or not to show completed tasks. Default: showCompleted=true

showDeleted.doc: Specify whether or not to show deleted tasks. Default: showDeleted=false

showHidden.doc: Specify whether or not to show hidden tasks. Default: showHidden=true

pageToken.doc: Token specifying the result page to return. The default is to return the first page.

updatedMin.doc: Lower bound for a task's last modification time (as an RFC 3339 timestamp) to filter by. Use the RFC 3339 timestamp format. For example: 2010-08-09T10:57:00.000-08:00Z. The default is not to filter by last modification time.

listUserTaskLists.doc: Returns all the authenticated user's Tasklist Resources. Authentication is required.

fields.doc: Selector specifying a subset of fields to include in the response. Use for better performance.

maxResults.doc: The maximum number of elements to return with this request. Default: maxResults=20. Maximum allowable value: maxResults=100.

pageToken.doc: Token specifying the result page to return. The default is to return the first page.

moveTask.doc: Moves the specified task to another position in the task list. This can include putting it as a child task under a new parent and/or moving it to a different position among its sibling tasks. Returns a copy of the updated Task Resource. Authentication is required.

tasklist.doc: Task list identifier. To refer to the authenticated user's default task list, use the special value @default.

previous.doc: Specify the task's previous task ID. No parameter indicates an insertion or a move to the first position in the sublist.

updateTask.doc: Updates the specified task. Returns a copy of the updated Task Resource. Authentication is required.
